underlying_goal: To commit and push a set of local changes to a new GitHub repository and open a pull request.
friction_detail: Claude first tried to push without a configured remote, then encountered sandbox permission issues when trying to add the remote to the git config. It successfully worked around this by providing the user with the exact commands to run manually.
primary_success: Despite hitting multiple obstacles (no remote, sandbox permissions), Claude successfully guided the user through creating a GitHub repo, configuring the remote, pushing a new branch, and creating a pull request.
brief_summary: The user wanted to commit and push changes. Claude identified that no remote was configured, guided the user to create a new GitHub repo, and despite hitting a sandbox permission issue, provided the correct manual commands. After the user switched the remote to SSH, Claude successfully pushed the branch and created the PR.
